article.headline: Reed's double-double helps Xavier get by St. Louis
article.linkText: No. 16 Xavier escapes for 15th straight victory
article.story:
ST. LOUIS -- Tudy Reed had 16 points and 11 rebounds to help Xavier (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) win its 15th straight game with a 70-67 victory over Saint Louis on Saturday.

Ta'Shia Phillips added 15 points and nine rebounds as Xavier (24-4, 12-0) remained unbeaten in the Atlantic 10. Jerri Taylor had 13 points for the Musketeers, who have won 12 straight over the Billikens.

Amanda Kemezys matched her career high with 22 points and Theresa Lisch added 16 points and a career-best nine assists for Saint Louis (11-16, 5-7).

Saint Louis entered the game heading in the opposite direction of the Musketeers, having lost four of its last five.

Lisch put the Billikens up 64-61 with a 3-pointer with 2:04 left. But the Musketeers scored the next seven, including a key putback by Phillips off a missed free throw with 18.5 seconds left that made it 68-64.
